<subSubSection id="C3616545FFFBBF11FF17402BFE16F8E5" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFFBBF11FF17402BFE16F8E5" blockId="25.[151,1436,1641,2026]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FF17402BFE95F91A" bold="true" box="[151,266,1641,1666]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The underplate of the large projection of the gonocoxite in the male of this species is almost indistinguishable from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FE7140CCFD10F93E" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[497,655,1677,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryganica">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FE7140CCFD10F93E" box="[497,655,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. phryganica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FD4840CCFCCCF93E" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[712,851,1677,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemmella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FD4840CCFCCCF93E" box="[712,851,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. gemmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its shape is somewhat intermediate between those two species (
<figureCitation id="13402A4BFFFBBF11FEA940F3FE1DF952" box="[297,386,1713,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 20. a, b" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1103,1125]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,183,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[168,1412,183,1084]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 20. a, b, male antennae, both from Karpathos; a, Seladonia cretella; b, S. phryganica; c, d, male genitalia in ventral view of S. cretella; c, Crete; d, Karpathos." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244989/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
Figs 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FEE240F3FE1DF952" box="[354,386,1713,1738]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
c,d). The best character to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FCAC40F0FC01F952" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[812,926,1713,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FCAC40F0FC01F952" box="[812,926,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. cretella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from both species is the long fourth antennal segment (length/width 1.44–1.53 in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FDB44094FD38F976" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[564,679,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FDB44094FD38F976" box="[564,679,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. cretella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 1.05–1.17 in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FCF04094FB91F976" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[880,1038,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryganica">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FCF04094FB91F976" box="[880,1038,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. phryganica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 1.41 in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FB204094FAB4F976" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[1184,1323,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemmella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FB204094FAB4F976" box="[1184,1323,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. gemmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; compare 
<figureCitation id="13402A4BFFFBBF11FF1740BBFEC5F88A" box="[151,346,1785,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 20. a, b" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1103,1125]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,183,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[168,1412,183,1084]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 20. a, b, male antennae, both from Karpathos; a, Seladonia cretella; b, S. phryganica; c, d, male genitalia in ventral view of S. cretella; c, Crete; d, Karpathos." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244989/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
Figs 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FF4E40BBFF75F889" box="[206,234,1785,1809]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="20.0">20</number>
a and 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FEAD40BBFED3F88A" box="[301,332,1785,1810]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="20.0">20</number>
b
</figureCitation>
). This species can also be recognized by its geographic distribution, as it is an endemic species to the islands of Karpathos and Crete. On these two islands, the antenna is dark ventrally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FB2B415CFA80F8AE" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[1195,1311,1821,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FB2B415CFA80F8AE" box="[1195,1311,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. cretella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while it is brown yellow throughout in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FE554100FDEFF8C2" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[469,624,1857,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryganica">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FE554100FDEFF8C2" box="[469,624,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. phryganica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13402A4BFFFBBF11FDFF4103FD7EF8C2" box="[639,737,1857,1882]" captionStart="FIGURE 20. a, b" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1103,1125]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,183,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[168,1412,183,1084]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 20. a, b, male antennae, both from Karpathos; a, Seladonia cretella; b, S. phryganica; c, d, male genitalia in ventral view of S. cretella; c, Crete; d, Karpathos." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244989/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FD334103FD4DF8C2" box="[691,722,1857,1882]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="20.0">20</number>
b
</figureCitation>
); the small projection of the gonocoxite is also not as thin as in that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FF664124FE1EF8E6" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[230,385,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryganica">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FF664124FE1EF8E6" box="[230,385,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. phryganica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616545FFFBBF11FF4741CBFB58F872" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFFBBF11FF4741CBFB58F872" blockId="25.[151,1436,1641,2026]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FF4741CBFECEF83A" bold="true" box="[199,337,1929,1954]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">Description</emphasis>
. Male and female as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFFBBF11FD5941C8FCE5F83A" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[729,890,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdula">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFFBBF11FD5941C8FCE5F83A" box="[729,890,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">S. smaragdula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows: underplate of large projection of male gonocoxite subtriangular to boomerang-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13402A4BFFFBBF11FCA041EFFCE4F85E" box="[800,891,1965,1990]" captionStart="FIGURE 20. a, b" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1103,1125]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,183,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[168,1412,183,1084]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 20. a, b, male antennae, both from Karpathos; a, Seladonia cretella; b, S. phryganica; c, d, male genitalia in ventral view of S. cretella; c, Crete; d, Karpathos." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244989/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
Figs 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FCDB41EFFCE4F85E" box="[859,891,1965,1990]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
c,d). Small projection of gonocoxite moderately thin (
<figureCitation id="13402A4BFFFBBF11FF524193FEBAF872" box="[210,293,2001,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="29.[151,250,856,878]" captionTargetBox="[179,1405,198,829]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[176,1411,193,834]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 24. Contour of the small projection, in lateral view, of the male gonocoxite in the species of the Seladonia smaragdula complex; a, S. smaragdula (Spain, Almeria); b, S. phryganica sp. nov. (Greece, Anafi); c, S. gemmella sp. nov. (Spain, Almeria); d, S. cretella sp. nov. (Greece, Crete); e, S. submediterranea sp. nov. (France, Deux-Sèvres); f, S. orientana sp. nov. (Greece, Lesvos)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244993/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="282">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB324E9FFFBBF11FE864193FEBAF872" box="[262,293,2001,2026]" pageId="25" pageNumber="282" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Fourth antennal segment of the male relatively long (length/width = 1.44–1.53).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF046646FFF8BF12FF17420DFDD7FB1C" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244989/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" targetBox="[171,1411,183,1075]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFF8BF12FF17420DFDD7FB1C" blockId="26.[151,1435,1103,1156]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFF8BF12FF17420DFEBFFBFD" bold="true" box="[151,288,1103,1125]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">FIGURE 20.</emphasis>
a, b, male antennae, both from Karpathos; a, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFF8BF12FD75420DFC32FBFD" authority="Robertson, 1918" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1918" box="[757,941,1103,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Seladonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretella">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFF8BF12FD75420DFC32FBFD" box="[757,941,1103,1125]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">
Seladonia 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFF8BF12FCE1420DFC32FBFD" box="[865,941,1103,1125]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" rank="species" species="cretella">cretella</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
